**Most critical gap**: The SOCKS5 domain name path (`ATYP=0x03`) in both `read_socks_connect_request` and `send_socks_connect_reply` is entirely untested for the success case. Domain names are the most common SOCKS5 target type (browsers proxy to hostnames, not raw IPs), so a bug here would silently break the primary use case of the socket relay.

**Overall test quality**: Generally very high across this batch. `rbac.rs`, `shutdown.rs`, and `webhook.rs` have excellent, well-named tests with meaningful assertions. `rate_limiter.rs` covers the main scenarios but misses boundary values. `sockets.rs` is thorough on lifecycle management but has a notable gap in the domain-name protocol path. `payload_builder.rs` has extensive tests (~80 test functions) covering all the compiler diagnostic parsers, toolchain validation, and cache management well.
